Russia’s Grain Exports Seen as High as 45 Million Tons by 2020

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-10-18T12:54:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/russia-s-grain-exports-seen-as-high-as-45-million-tons-by-2020.html
Russia ’s grain exports may reach 40
million to 45 million metric tons by 2020, state grain trader
United Grain Co. said.  Southeast Asian countries are among “priority
destinations” for export development, Aram Gukasyan, United
Grain’s deputy director general, said in a statement e-mailed
today. United Grain plans a grains terminal in Russia’s far
eastern region with the capacity to handle as much as 5 million
tons a year, as well as six grain silos in Siberia with a total
capacity of 1.5 million to 1.8 million tons a year, he said.  Gukasyan commented during a visit by a Russian grain
business delegation to  Tokyo  on Oct. 12, according to the
statement. The group was led by Evgeny Popov, deputy director of
the economy ministry’s department on Asia and  Africa .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
